    {
      "id": "23b7cc67_750ec86e",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ri/utils/CpsSessionFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 57,
      "message": "Since CpsSessionFactory is essentially just a wrapper around SessionFactory with single-line methods, it doesn't provide much value beyond what SessionFactory already offers.\n\nReasons to Remove CpsSessionFactory\n\n1. Direct Injection of SessionFactory\n\nSpring Boot (with Hibernate) already manages SessionFactory as a bean.\nWe can inject SessionFactory wherever needed and call openSession() or close() directly.\n\n2. Unnecessary Singleton Scope\n\nSessionFactory is already a singleton when managed by Spring. Wrapping it inside another singleton (CpsSessionFactory) adds no real benefit.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-13 17:18:18.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "39cebdf3_fb41afbb",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ri/utils/CpsSessionFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 57,
      "message": "the scope of this patch is to just resolve the problem we are getting during using CpsSessionFactory.\n\nCan get teams opinion on the refactoring later.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7965,
        "name": "Priyank Maheshwari",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "priyank.maheshwari@est.tech",
        "username": "mpriyank"
      },
      "updated": "2025-02-14 09:36:51.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "23b7cc67_750ec86e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "56557d72_9220f280",
      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ri/utils/CpsSessionFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 57,
      "message": "Understood. The immediate goal is to resolve the issue with CpsSessionFactory, and we can discuss refactoring later. That said, since SessionManager is the only class using CpsSessionFactory, replacing it directly with SessionFactory seems like a small and straightforward change. This could simplify things now rather than revisiting it later. Let me know what you think!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
